	<text id="ruskin_to_mother_july_03_1867">
	
	    <header>
	        <inventNo>1996L00308</inventNo>
	    </header>
	
	    <body>
	        <div type="text">
	            <pb n="1"/>
	            <opener>
	                <placeName><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="Q31105500" type="place">Huntly Burn</rs>
	                </placeName>
	                <date when="1867-07-05"><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs type="date">July 5th 1867</rs>
	                </date>
	                <salute>My dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">Mother</rs></salute><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	            </opener>
	
	            <p id="p1">
	                <s id="s1">I could not send you an envelope yesterday, for I did not know where I was going, but
	                    here is one for you.</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <p id="p2">
	                <s id="s2">I feel decidedly better for the change even under all disadvantage of weather and I
	                    hope to do better after this.</s>
	                <s id="s3">- The sun has come out today, and I am going to have a walk up <rs key="rhymers_glen"
	                                                                                              type="place">Rhymer's glen</rs> - with <rs key="m_kerr" type="person">Mary Kerr</rs> -
	                </s>
	                <s id="s4">If I were twenty years younger, it would be a complete scene for the <rs key="95207079"
	                                                                                                    type="person">Author of Waverley</rs> - the young Scottish lady, being a Roman Catholic making it still more perfect.
	                </s>
	            </p>
	
	            <closer>
	                <salute>For my dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">mother</rs> your <expan>affect<ex
	                        cert="high">ionate</ex>ate</expan> Son
	                    .</salute><!-- optional - delete if
		                unnecessary -->
	                <signed><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="73859585" type="person">J. Ruskin.</rs>
	                </signed>
	            </closer>
	
	            <postscript>
	                <p id="p3">
	                    <s id="s5"><rs key="8196344" type="person">Alice</rs> always asks affectionately for you, and sends
	                        you her love.</s>
	                    <s id="s6">She gains every day in health and intelligence.</s>
	                </p>
	                <p id="p4">
	                    <s id="s7">I had a pleasant talk with a rough <rs key="Q22" type="place">Scotch</rs> Stonemason
	                        and sculptor yesterday, a man of true genius, and some nice music in the evening.</s>
	                </p>
	            </postscript>
	
